# SQLAlchemy Alembic Standards

- Model changes require migration updates in the same change set.
- Keep table and column names explicit and stable for analytical workloads.
- Use nullable/index defaults intentionally; do not rely on implicit behavior.
- Ensure migrations are idempotent and reversible via `downgrade`.
- Run migration checks in CI for schema safety.
